I changed the sentence "Georgia is one of 14 states that use [[electronic voting machine]]s that produce no paper record, which election integrity experts say leaves elections vulnerable to tampering and technical problems." to reflect that Georgia NO LONGER uses voting machines without a paper record. Since 2020, Georgia has used Dominion's voting systems, which provide a paper record of every vote. https://faq.georgiavoter.guide/en/article/voting-on-georgias-new-voting-machines
